Believing that the true aim of Greek study is the development of the power to read Greek, the pupil is introduced at an early stage to practice in the translation of a continuous text, including dialogues, fables, and reading exercises.

The book is fully illustrated‚ and contains, in addition to the reading exercises given in the body of the book, selections from the Anabasi5‚ Hellenica, Cyropaedia‚ and Memorabilia, an Ap- pendix containing in compendious form for refer- ence the rules of euphony and syntax, and the paradigms of declension and conjugation given in the regular lessons.
